did.abstract: This collection is made up of directories to campus faculty and staff at the new York State College of Teachers and the University at Albany.
did.physloc: The materials are located onsite in the department.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: The New York State College for Teachers and the University at Albany provided contact information for faculty and staff by using campus directories. These directories were published yearly, as well as other version such as specific Summer session directories and one for specific departments. Publishing of these seems to have halted since the campus website provided all necessary contact information.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: In this collection are the directories dating from 1925 to 2006. The majority are general directories to the faculty and staff, though some have a more specific target from certain departments, as well as seasonal copies such as the summer telephone directories. The information provided is the list of faculty and staff members working in all aspects of the University, as well as how they can be reached with information like office locations and telephone numbers.

arrangement.head: Arrangement of the Collection
arrangement.p: The collection is organized topically and chronolgoically within those groups.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: All items in this manuscript group were donated to the University Libraries, M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives.
